FT  01 DEC 92 / UK Company News: United Drug
United Drug, the Irish pharmaceutical and consumer products group, increased
its pre-tax profit by nearly 15 per cent, from IPounds 2.69m to IPounds
3.09m, or Pounds 3.36m, in the year ended September 30 1992.
Turnover rose 21 per cent to IPounds 76.4m (IPounds 63m), reflecting
expansion into non-pharmaceutical areas combined with successful management
of the core pharmaceutical activities.
Each of the divisions reported satisfactory results. In particular
substantial profit growth was achieved in the pharmaceutical distribution
and consumer products sides.
Earnings per share came to 17.6p (15.88p). The final dividend is 4.65p for a
total of 6.7p (6.25p).
